text: Mahya Dağı (, Mahiada) (1031 m) is a mountain peak in Turkey. It is the highest peak of the Strandzha massif (Yıldız Mountains) and also the European part of Turkey. ==Gallery== View of Mahya Dağı from Bulgaria.
